# Available Specialized Agents

Use Task tool with appropriate subagent_type for complex work.

## Core Development

- **backend-dev-expert**: [Your backend framework], database, AI/ML, image processing
- **frontend-development-specialist**: [Your frontend framework], UI, forms, state management
- **testing-agent**: Unit/integration/E2E tests, coverage, flaky fixes
- **debugging-agent**: Bug investigation, root cause analysis, tracing

## Infrastructure

- **devops-specialist**: Docker, CI/CD, deployment, Nginx
- **security-specialist**: Security audits, hardening, vulnerabilities, compliance
- **system-infrastructure**: Network, VLANs, GPU setup, VPN

## Deployment

- **deployment-coordinator**: [Your hosting platforms] deployments, CI/CD generation, rollback

## Productivity

- **orchestrator-agent**: Complex multi-workstream projects (3+ parallel tasks)
- **doc-generator**: Technical docs, error logging, portfolio projects

## Built-in

- **Explore**: Fast codebase exploration
- **Plan**: Research and planning

## Quick Selection Guide

| Task Type                | Agent                            |
| ------------------------ | -------------------------------- |
| API endpoint with auth   | backend-dev-expert               |
| Frontend form validation | frontend-development-specialist  |
| Random test failures     | testing-agent or debugging-agent |
| Docker deployment        | devops-specialist                |
| Security audit           | security-specialist              |
| Network/GPU setup        | system-infrastructure            |

## Code Pattern References

Agents reference external pattern files for code examples:

- `~/.claude/agent-references/backend-patterns.md`
- `~/.claude/agent-references/frontend-patterns.md`
- `~/.claude/agent-references/devops-patterns.md`
- `~/.claude/agent-references/testing-patterns.md`

**When to use agents**: Complex tasks >15 minutes, systematic workflows, specialized domain expertise.
